# 🛒 Wellmart Sales Analysis Dashboard

## 📊 Project Overview
This project analyzes Wellmart retail sales data to understand store performance, seasonal trends, customer purchasing behavior, and the impact of external factors on sales.

It demonstrates an end-to-end data analytics workflow including data cleaning, statistical analysis, SQL-based querying, and interactive dashboard visualization.

---

## 🎯 Objective
- Analyze store performance and revenue trends
- Identify seasonal patterns in sales
- Understand the impact of external factors (CPI, Fuel Price, Temperature, Unemployment)
- Build an interactive dashboard for business insights

---

## 🛠 Tools & Technologies
- Python (Pandas, NumPy)
- SQL (MySQL)
- Microsoft Excel
- Power BI
- Statistics (Descriptive & Correlation Analysis)

---

## 🔄 Project Workflow

### 1️⃣ Data Cleaning & Preparation (Python)
- Cleaned and preprocessed dataset using Pandas
- Converted Date column into datetime format
- Created new features: Year, Month, Quarter
- Removed inconsistencies and ensured data quality

---

### 2️⃣ Statistical Analysis
- Calculated Mean, Median, and Standard Deviation
- Used Coefficient of Variation (CV) to analyze stability
- Performed correlation analysis between:
  - Fuel Price
  - CPI
  - Temperature
  - Unemployment
  - Weekly Sales

---

### 3️⃣ Database Integration (SQL)
- Loaded cleaned dataset into MySQL
- Performed queries to analyze:
  - Store performance
  - Year-wise revenue trends
  - Seasonal sales patterns
  - Holiday impact on sales

---

### 4️⃣ Data Visualization (Power BI)
- Built an interactive dashboard with:
  - Total Revenue KPI
  - Average Weekly Sales
  - Store Performance Analysis
  - Year-wise Revenue Comparison
  - Monthly Sales Trends
  - Holiday vs Non-Holiday Analysis
  - Interactive Filters (Year, Month, Store)

---

## 📈 Key Business Insights
- Store 20 generated the highest revenue (~301M)
- Store 33 generated the lowest revenue (~33M)
- 2011 recorded the highest total revenue (~2448M)
- July showed peak sales performance
- January recorded the lowest sales
- Holiday weeks had higher average sales than non-holiday periods

---

## 🚀 Conclusion
This project highlights how data analytics can be used to uncover trends, improve decision-making, and drive business performance through interactive dashboards.
